text.tspan: Deaths in state-based conflicts by world region
Included are deaths of soldiers and civilians from fighting, excluded are deaths from disease or famine.
State-based conflicts are between states, or a state and a non-state armed group.
Note: The sources' 'best' estimates are used, or - if unavailable - the mid-point between high and low
Data source: OWID based on PRIO and UCDP
